<%- include('partials/header') %>

<section class="py-16 px-6" style="background-color: var(--studio-cream); min-height: 100vh;">
  <div class="max-w-6xl" style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 5rem;">
    
    <!-- 1. Page Header -->
    <div class="section-header">
      <p class="sub">Our Heritage</p>
      <h2>About the Sculptor & Studio</h2>
      <div class="divider"></div>
      <p class="desc">The legacy of handmade clay idols crafted with devotion, mud, and water in Bhiti Mau, Uttar Pradesh.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- 2. Biography Bio Section -->
    <div class="bio-grid grid">
      <div class="bio-image-wrapper">
        <img src="images/Gemini_Generated_Image_v4xz2kv4xz2kv4xz.png" alt="Jeetendra Prajapati Clay Art Portrait" />
      </div>

      <div class="bio-text">
        <h3>Jeetendra Prajapati: <br /><span class="italic-gold" style="font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 400; font-family: var(--font-playfair); color: var(--studio-gold);">A Lifetime Dedicated to Earth</span></h3>
        <div class="divider"></div>
        <p>
          For over two decades, Jeetendra Prajapati has sculpted custom artworks, large-scale temple panels, and festival idols. In a world increasingly dominated by mass-produced plastic and toxic Plaster of Paris (PoP) molds, our studio stands committed to authentic hand-sculpted clay (Mitti).
        </p>
        <p>
          Based in Bhiti Mau, Mau (Uttar Pradesh), our workshop serves as both a training ground for local youth and a production studio for clients across the country seeking custom spiritual and decorative art.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- 3. Quality pillars grid -->
    <div class="grid" style="grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(240px, 1fr)); gap: 1.5rem;">
      <!-- Eco Friendly -->
      <div class="service-card" style="padding: 2rem 1.5rem;">
        <div class="icon-wrapper">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="28" height="28" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M12 2L2 7l10 5 10-5-10-5z"></path><path d="M2 17l10 5 10-5"></path><path d="M2 12l10 5 10-5"></path></svg>
        </div>
        <h4 style="font-family: var(--font-playfair); font-size: 1.125rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">100% Eco-Friendly</h4>
        <p style="font-size: 0.8125rem;">Our idols dissolve naturally in water within hours during immersion (Visarjan), leaving zero toxic chemical residues.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- 20 Years Legacy -->
      <div class="service-card" style="padding: 2rem 1.5rem;">
        <div class="icon-wrapper">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="28" height="28" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><circle cx="12" cy="8" r="7"></circle><polyline points="8.21 13.89 7 23 12 20 17 23 15.79 13.88"></polyline></svg>
        </div>
        <h4 style="font-family: var(--font-playfair); font-size: 1.125rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">20+ Years Legacy</h4>
        <p style="font-size: 0.8125rem;">Over 20 years of experience in making beautiful and traditional clay idols with great attention to detail.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Custom Commissioned -->
      <div class="service-card" style="padding: 2rem 1.5rem;">
        <div class="icon-wrapper">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="28" height="28" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M20.84 4.61a5.5 5.5 0 0 0-7.78 0L12 5.67l-1.06-1.06a5.5 5.5 0 0 0-7.78 7.78l1.06 1.06L12 21.23l7.78-7.78 1.06-1.06a5.5 5.5 0 0 0 0-7.78z"></path></svg>
        </div>
        <h4 style="font-family: var(--font-playfair); font-size: 1.125rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Custom Commissioned</h4>
        <p style="font-size: 0.8125rem;">No molds are ever used. Every statue is built from scratch, tailoring poses, facial lines, and sizes to your vision.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Temple Grade -->
      <div class="service-card" style="padding: 2rem 1.5rem;">
        <div class="icon-wrapper">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="28" height="28" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M22 11.08V12a10 10 0 1 1-5.93-9.14"></path><polyline points="22 4 12 14.01 9 11.01"></polyline></svg>
        </div>
        <h4 style="font-family: var(--font-playfair); font-size: 1.125rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Temple Grade</h4>
        <p style="font-size: 0.8125rem;">Our idols are made following traditional Hindu art and culture, with great care and attention to detail.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- 4. Creation workflow process -->
    <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 3rem;">
      <div class="section-header" style="margin-bottom: 1rem;">
        <h2>From Clay to Beautiful Idols</h2>
        <p class="desc">Discover the careful steps that go into transforming raw riverbank mud into a spiritual masterpiece.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="step-grid grid">
        <!-- Step 1 -->
        <div class="step-card">
          <span class="step-number">01</span>
          <h4>Clay Sourcing & Prep</h4>
          <p>We source high-grade river clay (mitti) from local riverbeds. The clay is cleaned of pebbles, mixed with water, and kneaded extensively to achieve perfect plasticity.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Step 2 -->
        <div class="step-card">
          <span class="step-number">02</span>
          <h4>Wood & Straw armature</h4>
          <p>A wooden framework (armature) is constructed to support the weight. Organic straw and jute fibers are bound tightly around the wood to form the core mass of the sculpture.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Step 3 -->
        <div class="step-card">
          <span class="step-number">03</span>
          <h4>Clay Layering & Detail</h4>
          <p>The mud mixture is applied in layers. The initial layer establishes the anatomy, while the final layer is applied by Jeetendra Prajapati to define details like eyes, facial expressions, and clothing folds.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Step 4 -->
        <div class="step-card">
          <span class="step-number">04</span>
          <h4>Sun Drying & Dyes</h4>
          <p>Idols are dried naturally in the sun to prevent cracking. No chemical baking is used. Finally, the sculpture is painted using bio-degradable natural dyes and chalk colors.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>

<%- include('partials/footer') %>
